strings : swapPairs

Write a method named swapPairs that accepts a string as a parameter and returns a new string such that each pair of adjacent letters will 
be reversed. If the string has an odd number of letters, the last letter is unchanged. For example, if a string variable s stores "example", 
the call of swapPairs(s); should return "xemalpe". If s had been "hello there", the call would produce "ehll ohtree".

 public static String swapPairs(String str) {
        String[] string = new String[str.length()];
        for(int i = 0; i < string.length; i++) {
            string[i] = String.valueOf(str.charAt(i));
        }

        for(int i = 0; i < string.length - 1; i+=2) {
            String temp = string[i + 1];
            string[i + 1] = string[i];
            string[i] = temp;
        }

        return String.join("", string);

    }



